## 12. Additional Recommendations

### Security Headers

Implement security headers in middleware:

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/SecurityHeaders.php
public function handle($request, Closure $next)
{
    $response = $next($request);
    
    $response->headers->set('X-Frame-Options', 'SAMEORIGIN');
    $response->headers->set('X-Content-Type-Options', 'nosniff');
    $response->headers->set('X-XSS-Protection', '1; mode=block');
    $response->headers->set('Strict-Transport-Security', 'max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains');
    $response->headers->set('Referrer-Policy', 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin');
    $response->headers->set('Permissions-Policy', 'geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()');
    
    return $response;
}
```

### Content Security Policy

```php
$response->headers->set('Content-Security-Policy', 
    "default-src 'self'; " .
    "script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; " .  // Adjust as needed
    "style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' fonts.googleapis.com; " .
    "font-src 'self' fonts.gstatic.com; " .
    "img-src 'self' data: https:; " .
    "connect-src 'self'"
);
```

### Backup Security

**Location:** [BackupController.php](file:///c:/Users/USER/Documents/GitHub/fgei-sms/app/Http/Controllers/BackupController.php)

- ✅ Spatie Backup package used
- ⚠️ Ensure backups are encrypted
- ⚠️ Store backups off-site (S3, Azure Blob)
- ⚠️ Test restoration procedures regularly

